    "title": {
      "rendered": "6 Technology Concepts Nonprofits Need to Understand in 2018"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-22134\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Technology-Concepts-Nonprofits-2018-Facebook-1-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Technology-Concepts-Nonprofits-2018-Facebook-1.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Technology-Concepts-Nonprofits-2018-Facebook-1.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Technology-Concepts-Nonprofits-2018-Facebook-1.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Technology-Concepts-Nonprofits-2018-Facebook-1.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Technology-Concepts-Nonprofits-2018-Facebook-1.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />Over the last decade the discussion around nonprofit technology (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/nptech\"><strong>#nptech</strong></a>) has primarily been social media, mobile technology, and online fundraising, however as the internet enters its next phase, nonprofits need to better understand some of the more complicated concepts that will shape the internet and its use in the decades to come.</p>\n<p>Advancements in internet technology will change how we live, how we serve, how we fundraise, and how we interact with humans, the natural world, and machines.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>1. Blockchain\u00a0\u2013 <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/blockchainforgood\">#blockchainforgood</a></h1>\n<p>A\u00a0blockchain\u00a0is a decentralized, distributed and public digital ledger that is used to record transactions across many computers so that the record cannot be altered retroactively without the alteration of all subsequent blocks and the collusion of the network. &#8211; <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blockchain\"><strong>Wikipedia</strong></a></p>\n<p><center><iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/r43LhSUUGTQ\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></center><center></center><br />\n<strong>NTEN: <a href=\"https://www.nten.org/article/restoring-trust-with-blockchain/\">Restoring Trust in the Nonprofit Sector with Blockchain<br />\n</a>Social Media Week: <a href=\"https://socialmediaweek.org/blog/2018/01/essential-guide-blockchain-brands/\">The Essential Guide to Blockchain for Brands<br />\n</a>Bond: <a href=\"https://www.bond.org.uk/news/2017/10/top-11-resources-on-blockchain-for-global-development\">Top 11 Resources on Blockchain for Global Development</a></strong></p>\n<h1>2. Cryptocurrency\u00a0\u2013 <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/cryptoforgood\">#cryptoforgood</a></h1>\n<p>A cryptocurrency is a digital or virtual currency that uses cryptography for security. A cryptocurrency is difficult to counterfeit because of this security feature. A defining feature of a cryptocurrency, and arguably its most endearing allure, is its organic nature; it is not issued by any central authority, rendering it theoretically immune to government interference or manipulation. &#8211; <a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/cryptocurrency.asp\"><strong>Investopedia</strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.investing.com/crypto/currencies\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22090\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Cryptocurrency-Nonprofit-2.jpg?resize=600%2C368\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Cryptocurrency-Nonprofit-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Cryptocurrency-Nonprofit-2.jpg?resize=300%2C184&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong>As of 2/26/18: Number of Cryptocurrencies:\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.investing.com/crypto/currencies\">1,577</a>\u00a0Total Market Cap:\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.investing.com/crypto/currencies\">$450,941,873,379</a></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Tech Impact: <a href=\"http://blog.techimpact.org/bitcoin-and-blockchain-provides-transparency-for-donations\">Bitcoin and Blockchain Provides Transparency for Donations</a><br />\nBeaconfire RED: <a href=\"http://www.beaconfire-red.com/epic-stuff/should-nonprofits-accept-bitcoin-donations\">Should Nonprofits Accept Bitcoin and Other Cyrptocurrencies?<br />\n</a>Cryptocurrencies to Watch: <a href=\"https://www.giftcoin.org\">Gift Coin</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.missioncoin.org\">Mission Coin</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.ngoxchange.com\">NGO Coin</a>,\u00a0<a href=\"https://wishcoin.io\">Wishcoin</a></strong></p>\n<h1>3. Artificial Intelligence\u00a0\u2013<strong>\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/aiforgood\">#aiforgood</a></strong></h1>\n<p>Artificial intelligence (AI) is an area of computer science that emphasizes the creation of intelligent machines that work and react like humans. &#8211; <strong><a href=\"https://www.techopedia.com/definition/190/artificial-intelligence-ai\">Techopedia</a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.reviewcentralme.com/2017/08/03/infographics-uae-consumers-rank-high-appetite-artificial-intelligence/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22106\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/3.jpg?resize=600%2C334\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/3.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/3.jpg?resize=300%2C167&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong>SAS:\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.sas.com/en_us/insights/analytics/what-is-artificial-intelligence.html\">Artificial Intelligence: What It Is and Why It Matters<br />\n</a>Charity Digital News: <a href=\"https://www.charitydigitalnews.co.uk/2018/02/20/artificial-intelligence-future-charity-sector/\">Artificial Intelligence: The Future of the Charity Sector<br />\n</a>Nonprofit Quarterly:\u00a0<a href=\"https://nonprofitquarterly.org/2017/05/18/tech-giants-join-forces-nonprofits-establish-share-ai-best-practices/\">Tech Giants Join with Nonprofits to Consider AI Practice</a></strong></p>\n<h1>4. Encryption &#8211;\u00a0<strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/encryptionforgood\">#encryptionforgood</a></strong></h1>\n<p>Data encryption translates data into another form, or code, so that only people with access to a secret key (decryption key) or password can read it. &#8211; <a href=\"https://digitalguardian.com/blog/what-data-encryption\"><strong>Digital Guardian</strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22111\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/nonprofits-encryption-technology.jpg?resize=600%2C600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/nonprofits-encryption-technology.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/nonprofits-encryption-technology.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/nonprofits-encryption-technology.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/nonprofits-encryption-technology.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/nonprofits-encryption-technology.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Upwork:\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/hiring/development/introduction-to-encryption-data-security/\">Encryption Basics: How It Works &amp; Why You Need It<br />\n</a>Nonprofit Risk Management Center: <a href=\"https://www.nonprofitrisk.org/resources/articles/data-privacy-and-cyber-liability-what-you-dont-know-puts-your-mission-at-risk/\">Data Privacy and Cyber Liability<br />\n</a>Public Interest Registry: <a href=\"http://pir.org/ngos-and-data-security-what-to-do-in-the-aftermath-of-data-breach/\">What to Do in the Aftermath of a Data Breach</a></strong></p>\n<h1>5. Internet of Things\u00a0\u2013 <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/iotforgood\">#iotforgood</a></h1>\n<p>The\u00a0Internet of things\u00a0(IoT) is the network of physical devices, vehicles, home appliances and other items embedded with electronics, software, sensors, actuators, and connectivity which enables these objects to connect and exchange data. &#8211; <strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_of_things\">Wikipedia</a></strong></p>\n<p><center><iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QSIPNhOiMoE\" width=\"600\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></center><strong><br />\nLinkedIn Group: <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12078228\">The Internet of Things for Nonprofit Organizations</a><br />\nInternet Society: <a href=\"https://www.internetsociety.org/resources/doc/2015/iot-overview\">The Internet of Things: An Overview</a><br />\n</strong><strong>Nonprofit Tech for Good:\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/05/29/5-ways-the-internet-of-things-could-transform-fundraising/\">5 Ways the Internet of Things Could Transform Fundraising</a></strong></p>\n<h1><strong>6. Cloud Computing\u00a0</strong>\u2013<strong>\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/cloudforgood\">#cloudforgood</a></strong></h1>\n<p>Cloud computing means storing and accessing data and programs over the Internet instead of software and hardware installed at your organization\u2019s physical location. &#8211; <a href=\"https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2372163,00.asp\"><strong>PC Magazine</strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20120913005362/en/Global-Survey-Reveals-NGOs-Moving-Cloud\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22098\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/NGOs-and-the-Could.png?resize=600%2C419\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"419\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/NGOs-and-the-Could.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/NGOs-and-the-Could.png?resize=300%2C210&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>TechSoup Global:\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20120913005362/en/Global-Survey-Reveals-NGOs-Moving-Cloud\">Global Survey Reveals Why NGOs Are Moving IT to the Cloud</a></strong><br />\n<strong>Charity Digital News:\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.charitydigitalnews.co.uk/2018/02/19/staying-safe-in-the-cloud-infographic/\">[INFOGRAPHIC] Staying Safe in the Cloud</a></strong><br />\n<strong>npEngage:\u00a0<a href=\"https://npengage.com/nonprofit-technology/why-is-the-cloud-right-for-your-nonprofit/\">Why is the Cloud Right for Your Nonprofit<br />\n</a></strong></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Newly Released! The 2018 Global NGO Technology Report</h2>\n<p>Published in \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651\u0629, English, fran\u00e7ais, portugu\u00eas y espa\u00f1ol, the <strong><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo\">2018 Global NGO Technology Report</a></strong>\u00a0is based on the survey results of 5,352 NGOs from 164 countries.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22066\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=600%2C315\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
